verbose_text: The antioxidant activity (AA) was expressed as the percentage of inhibition of beta-carotene bleaching, as compared to the control, and calculated using the following formula : AA (%) = [1 - (A S 0 - A S 120 / A C 0 - A C 120)] x 100 where A S and A C represent the A 470 value of the sample and control, respectively, and the superscript numbers denote the time of the initial and final measurement (0 and 120 min).
